Combine two cooked ingredients (e.g., cooked protein + cooked vegetable) to get a 60 value item. Then, add a third ingredient, often a grain, to that combined item to reach 80 value. Do NOT combine more than three ingredients in total or apply tools to your combined dishes, as this drastically reduces value. The 'water' tool can sometimes make raw or simply cooked grains valuable, but it will likely destroy complex dishes.

message: Focus on using the 'stove' tool. Cooking proteins and vegetables with the stove will give them a value of 20. Combining two cooked items (protein + vegetable is a good start) typically results in a 60 value. For the highest score, combine three cooked items  aim for one protein, one vegetable, and another cooked item (even if a cooked grain is 0 value, it still contributes to the 3-item combo)  to reach 80. Going beyond three ingredients seems to 'overcomplicate' and can lower the value.
